<PLUGIN name="&name;" author="&author;" version="&version;" min="7.0.0" launch="&launch;" pluginURL="&pluginURL;" icon="appdata.cleanup.plus.png" support="https://forums.unraid.net/topic/197975-plugin-appdata-cleanup-plus/">

<CHANGES>
###2026.07.08.32
- Safety: Protect appdata folders referenced by Docker Compose Manager projects so stopped/down compose stacks are not mistaken for orphaned cleanup candidates.
- Safety: Add an explicit Docker engine health check so scans fail closed when Docker appears running but container inventory cannot be verified.
- Safety: Skip filesystem discovery when a live container mounts an entire configured appdata root, avoiding broad false positives from root-level bind mounts.
- ZFS: Tighten recursive destroy previews so recursive deletion is only offered for child dataset, snapshot, dependent, or clone cases, not unrelated dry-run failures like busy datasets.
- Test: Extend behavior smoke coverage for Compose Manager protection, unresolved compose bind locks, Docker inventory verification, and non-escalating ZFS dry-run failures.

###2026.07.08.31
- UI: Remove the Plugin Settings button and modal completely; Safe Mode is controlled only from the top-right Safe Mode card.
- ZFS: Keep exact ZFS dataset cleanup enabled by default and force older saved settings to enabled so dataset rows can appear in Ready to Clean with a ZFS dataset source badge.

###2026.07.08.30
- Release feed: Remove accidental manifest conflict markers from the main feed and publish a clean package version.
- Release guard: Fail builds if conflict markers are present in manifest, CA metadata, source, or scripts.

###2026.07.08.29
- CI: Initialize the smoke-test PHP session after temporary state cleanup so GitHub Actions can persist snapshots and complete behavior validation.

###2026.07.08.28
- CI: Prepare writable /mnt/user, /mnt/fcache, and /mnt/docker_vm_nvme fixture roots before the behavior smoke test so GitHub Actions matches the Unraid path assumptions.

###2026.07.08.27
- Repo badges: Add the missing GitHub Actions CI workflow so the README CI badge resolves and reports real validation status.
- License: Add a standard root LICENSE file and update README license links so GitHub and shields detect MIT correctly.

###2026.07.08.26
- Layout: Prevent the dashboard from stretching empty vertical space when the browser is zoomed far out by packing the grid to the top.
- Loading state: Reduce the reserved results loading height so rescans do not create oversized blank gaps.

###2026.07.08.25
- Release notes: Replace the generic July dev-build placeholders with actual user-facing notes for each UI, deletion, modal, README, and feed update.
- Build guard: Require real changelog notes whenever a new package version is generated so future dev pushes cannot ship placeholder release history.

###2026.07.08.24
- Critical fix: Rework cleanup deletion back to the simple shell-backed behavior proven by the original Cleanup Appdata plugin so permanent delete and quarantine jobs complete reliably instead of throwing backend-busy/internal-server errors.
- UX overhaul: Replace the confusing review-heavy dashboard with a much simpler Ready to Clean workflow, fewer decisions, clearer Safe Mode behavior, and a table that explains what will happen without making users decode lock states.
- UI overhaul: Rebuild the dashboard around the mockup-aligned header, summary cards, action bar, ready table, compact badges, folder icons, size column, sticky bottom action bar, and Unraid theme-aware colors.
- Simplification: Remove the saved-template and outside-share cleanup gates from the normal workflow, remove the redundant Needs Review/Blocked flow, remove extra filter/status bars, and keep found folders actionable in one Ready to Clean list.
- Delete workflow: Add checkbox-based permanent-delete confirmation, live delete progress, disabled completion actions while deletion is running, clearer warning/results screens, and compact result summaries.
- Modals: Redesign Details, Appdata Sources, Quarantine, Audit History, Tools, delete confirmation, delete progress, and delete results dialogs so they match the new UI and are easier to understand.
- Polish: Tighten badge sizing/alignment, button colors, card alignment, safe-mode shield/status placement, source-column layout, folder icons, age labels, empty-folder size labels, and loading layout stability.
- Docs: Replace the README banner, rebuild the README to match FolderView Plus, align badges, remove developer-only sections, and add the MIT license.
- Safety retained: Keep server-side scan snapshots, candidate-id actions, CSRF validation, protected path locks, restore collision checks, quarantine tracking, and ZFS dataset-delete safeguards in place.

###2026.07.08.23
- Release prep: Refresh the dev feed and archive metadata for the stable main promotion after the UI, deletion, modal, README, and safety updates were complete.

